<HL>
   Pittston Unit's Acquisition
</HL>
<DATE>
05/01/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6
</SO>
<CO>
   PCO
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   GREENWICH, Conn. -- Pittston Co. said its Brink's Inc.
unit purchased all the shares it didn't already own in an
air-courier and armored-car company based in the United
Kingdom. Terms weren't disclosed.
   Brink's, which previously owned 35% of Brink's-MAT Ltd.,
London, purchased the remaining 65% from its partner, MAT
Group Ltd. Brink's-MAT, which operates in several European
countries as well as in Bahrain and Hong Kong, had revenue of
about $65 million last year.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Pittston is a coal, security and transportation concern.
</TEXT>
